Configmaps:
Store configuration data for an app
Hard-coding values(URL's, env, ports)

Stores:
Env variables
Configuration files
Key-value pairs
Will not store passwords, tokens.

Pods use configmaps:
	1. As env variables.
	2. Command line arguments.

Why?
	1. Keep configuration seperatly to code.
	2. Change configuration without rebuilding image.



